.eco is a [[top-level domain]] (TLD). It was proposed in [[ICANN]]'s [[Generic top-level domain#New top-level domains|new generic top-level domain (gTLD) program]] and became available to the general public on April 25, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.home.eco/eco-domain-launches-with-support-of-wwf-conservation-international-united-nations-global-compact-f2bce0d53b7e|title=.eco Domain Launches with Support of WWF, Conservation International, United Nations Global Compact…|date=2017-04-25|work=News {{!}} .eco|access-date=2017-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/annefield/2017/05/10/a-new-internet-extension-for-eco-conscious-companies/#51af1a709d6e|title=A New Internet Extension For Eco-Conscious Companies|last=Field|first=Anne|work=Forbes|access-date=2017-07-07}}</ref>
Big Room is the [[Domain name registry|registry]] for the domain and names can be registered at [http://go.eco go.eco].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.icann.org/resources/agreement/eco-2016-07-08-en|title=.eco Registry Agreement - ICANN|website=www.icann.org|language=en|access-date=2017-07-06}}</ref> The company won the rights through a community application after assembling a coalition of more than 50 environmental organizations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/dot-eco-meet-vancouver-team-behind-new-green-turf-1.3819802|title=Birth of an .eco empire: The story behind the internet's new green turf|work=CBC News|access-date=2017-07-07|language=en}}</ref> The registry is advised by a council of these organizations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/40418607/care-about-the-environment-get-yourself-a-fancy-new-eco-website|title=Care About The Environment? Get Yourself A Fancy New .Eco Website|date=2017-05-10|work=Fast Company|access-date=2017-07-07|language=en-US}}</ref>
